Date: Mon, 6 Apr 1998 15:03:29 +0100
From: Jill Banks <jbanks.cvl.wood@gtnet.gov.uk>

The avian influenza isolates from Ireland are of the H7N7 subtype. They do
not have multiple basic amino acids at the haemagglutinin cleavage site that
would be indicative of a highly pathogenic virus and the intravenous
pathogenicity index is 0. The Monaghan isolate is still being sequenced but
I don't expect it to be different from the others [from Ireland that the CVL
has examined.
--
Jill Banks
CVL/MAFF
New Haw, Surrey
ENGLAND
e-mail: jbanks.cvl.wood@gtnet.gov.uk
